        About this item

        • Quality is in our DNA: Tru Niagen is not only highly efficacious, its also extremely safe. Our key ingredient Niagen was successfully notified to the FDA three timestwice as an NDI (New Dietary Ingredient), and once as GRAS (Generally Recognized As Safe). Every batch is made in the United States and tested for potency and safety. A total of 22 tests (internal and third-party) are conducted in the testing and release of Tru Niagen.
        • Tru Niagen embodies 20+ years of scientific innovation around healthy aging. Our full-body supernutrient, Niagen, supports the 37.2 trillion cells in your body by boosting levels of NAD+ (nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide), a molecule thats vital to life as we know it. Niagen is a patented form of nicotinamide riboside (NR), and one of the most efficient NAD-boosting ingredients available. Backed by 40+ owned and licensed patents, 300+ published scientific studies, and 2 Nobel Prize winners.
        • Protect your healthspan with comprehensive cellular defense. Healthspan is the ability to stay healthy as you get oldersomething everyone desires. We support your healthspan by boosting your levels of NAD+, which naturally decline as you age. NAD+ is vital for cells to function optimally and stay resilient in the face of lifes many stressors. Tru Niagen is the most efficient, safe way to increase your NAD+ and support your bodys many systems and functions as you age.
        • What to expect: Using Tru Niagen daily to boost your cellular NAD+ can have many positive effects. Thousands of customers report overall improvements in general health and well-being. Everyones experience is different, because we all experience different types and levels of stress. What you feel and how long it takes will depend on what your cells need. Tru Niagen is clinically proven to elevate NAD+ levels by approximately 40-50% after 8 weeks.**
        • Scientifically proven: With consistent daily use, Tru Niagen is proven to raise NAD+ levels, as is shown by multiple published clinical trials, with 40+ registered human studies ongoing. In addition, studies support that Niagen (the key ingredient in Tru Niagen) is more efficient at raising NAD+ levels than nicotinamide/niacinamide, and niacin. The chemical structure of Niagen allows for more efficient absorption and utilization than other NAD+ precursors.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        Ive been taking Tru Niagen for over 5 years. The first 2 years I took 300mg/day but then increased due to the studies which say that your NAD boost is dose dependent. I had blood work done last year and its either the same or better than all my blood work going back 14 years.

A few examples are: in over 5 years, I just dont have those brain fog days after lunch. Instead when I want to focus on work, I just focus on work. I dont watch the clock, hoping for bedtime to arrive. I feel resilient. I believe that Tru Niagen helps with immune response. It continues to amaze me that in over 5 years, Ive taken 2 sick days at work. I also feel like it helps my hair, nails and skin.

        You do need to just take it regularly and wait a couple months. For me it took maybe 6 months before I felt like numerous benefits were noticeable.

        Also, you need to know its not going to make you a super hero. Its not a quick fix for an unhealthy lifestyle. You do need to really pay attention to your body to notice. For me, I noticed by observing my life honestly and saying wow this is a time when I remember saying no to things before - no thanks Im not feeling up for a night out, no Im too tired to clean out the garage today, no lets not goto the park and throw the football around. Like for example, waking up at 5am, driving the family to whitewater rafting, rafting till about noon, take the family to lunch, drive back to the cabin, clean the cabin for 3 hours, load up the family and drive home arriving at 11pm where I wasnt drowsy at all on that drive. At the end of days like that I think wow, this is the kind of stuff I did in my 20s. I just feel good. But its really hard to pin this to Tru Niagen unless you take it over a long enough time and take a very high level and honest view of your own life. Anyway thats how I was ultimately convinced.

        Because I care about what I put in my body regularly, I follow who else believes in Tru Niagen, and I have looked into where it is made etc.

        Tru Niagen has the FDA NDI and GRAS designations, as well as NSF certification (pro athletes can take it). Its worth noting that NMN for example (a different NAD booster), has actually been banned for sale as a dietary supplement in the USA.

        Tru Niagen is as of now, the only NAD booster I know of thats actually made in the USA. I want to be able to trace my supplements right to where they are made and I can do that with Tru Niagen.

        Its public knowledge that the Chiefs, Buccaneers, Patriots and Yankees all take Niagen. That means five of the last ten teams to play in the Super Bowl, and four out of the last five winners, take Tru Niagen.

        Its also worth knowing that Nestle is a part owner of Tru Niagen. So this is a reputable company.

        I dont think any of the other NAD booster brands come close to Tru Niagen in the above ways.

        Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2018
        Verified Purchase
        Tru Niagen works best if you are over the age of 40, or feel tired, or are under a lot of stress. Otherwise, if you are young, or if you are already extremely healthy, then you might not notice any results.

        This is a trial size bottle, for 2 weeks. Some people can tell within the first 2 weeks, whether or not Tru Niagen will help them. Other people notice the effects after about 1 month, or 3 months. The effects are very gentle, and happen slowly over time.

        The first week that I took Tru Niagen, I felt that the quality of my sleep improved in a major way. It seemed to me that I was dreaming more vividly, and getting to a deeper level of sleep. By the second week I noticed that my skin was clearing up.

        I have taken Niagen vitamin B3 for about 2 years now. It's the best vitamin supplement I have ever taken. I have better sleep quality, better skin, stronger nails, better eyesight, less gray hair, better liver/kidney/cholesterol numbers on lab tests, and less brain fog.

        After the first month, it became hard for me to sleep more than about 5 hours a night, so I started taking Niagen in a split dose early in the day at 6 am and noon, along with Doctor's Best 5-HTP Enhanced. The 5-HTP helps to build serotonin (to feel good) and melatonin (to sleep better).
         Doctor's Best 5-HTP Enhanced with Vitamins B6 and C, Non-GMO, Vegan, Gluten Free, Soy Free, 120 Veggie Caps

        I also feel better if I take a Stress B Complex capsule, from Thorne. Thorne's B6 is better than anybody else's B6.
         Thorne Research - Stress B-Complex - Vitamin B Complex for Stress Support - 60 Capsules

        I felt a lot of great effects from these 3 supplements (Tru Niagen, 5-HTP, and Stress B Complex) but I didn't get any more energy, until I added in Tyrosine by Thorne. The Tyrosine (amino acid) doesn't work unless you avoid protein for about an hour, before and after you take the Tyrosine, but carbs are okay. So I take the Tyrosine by itself first thing in the morning, along with some orange juice or D-Ribose powder in coffee.
         Thorne Research - L-Tyrosine - Amino Acid Supplement to Support Production of Dopamine and Norepinephrine - 90 Capsules
        BulkSupplements Pure D-Ribose Powder (1 Kilogram)

        I got some leg cramps at first when I was taking Tru Niagen, but they went away after I took Magnesium Citrate.

        If you want to scientifically measure how taking Tru Niagen is affecting you, then you can take a lab test from Lab Corp or Quest, before & after you take the Tru Niagen. Be sure to include tests for cholesterol levels, liver function (ALT & AST), kidney function (creatinine), and vitamin D level. First take the lab test, then take Tru Niagen for 3 months, and finally re-test again. Lab tests are available inexpensively online at LifeExtension.com (<$50), or they can be taken at your doctor's office.

        The 250 mg daily dose/serving of Tru Niagen found on the bottle label, is for someone who weighs about 184 pounds or less. That works out to 1.36 mg of Tru Niagen per pound, per day (or 3 mg of Tru Niagen per kg.) If you weigh more than 184 pounds, then you may need to take a higher dosage of Tru Niagen, to notice any effects.

        If you are not healthy, or if you take anti-depressants (like SSRIs), then you should talk with your doctor before you try this vitamin B3. Some people say that they have fewer food/beverage cravings, and don't get hungover so much from liquor, when they take Tru Niagen. Everybody reports slightly different results, from taking Tru Niagen.

        One last thing to remember, is that you might want to take it easy with the caffeine for a while. The same amount of coffee you drank before, might give you a pounding heart, after you start taking Tru Niagen. Same thing with carbs, and sugar. (Less is more.)
